                <p>
            <pb/>Colonel C. J. Napier has been appointed Governor <lb/>of the embryo colony
                    in South Australia, and we be<lb break="no"/>lieve that a fitter appointment
                    could not have been <lb/>made. We only regret that Colonel Napier has not
                    <lb/>been sent to superintend a colony founded on some<lb break="no"/>thing like
                    sane principles. But if this Austra<lb break="no"/>
            <lb/>lian project end, as we
                    have little doubt it will do, <lb/>in the ruin of those who are weak and silly
                    enough to <lb/>embark in it, no one will ascribe any part of the fail<lb break="no"/>ure to the incapacity or unfitness of the Governor. <lb/>The
                    whole blame will fall on the contrivers of the <lb/>scheme. </p>
